2. Tesh RB, Wilson ML, Salas R: Field studies on the epidemiology of Venezuelan hemorrhagic fever: implication of the cotton rat _Sigmodon alstoni_ as the probable rodent reservoir. Am J Trop Med Hyg. 1993 Aug; 49(2): 227-35; abstract available at http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/8395143.
3. Tesh RB, Jahrling PB, Salas R, Shope RE: Description of Guanarito virus (_Arenaviridae_: Arenavirus), the etiologic agent of Venezuelan hemorrhagic fever. Am J Trop Med Hyg. 1994 Apr; 50(4): 452-9; abstract available at http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/8166352.
